When choosing a soap you want to pick one that is not harsh to the skin. Harsh soaps can dry out the skin causing "special safe harbors" for bacteria and viruses to hide in making it very difficult to get a good kill on the skin. Traditional antimicrobial / antibacterial soaps contain quarts (quaternary ammonia) compounds which carry very alkaline (high pH's) although effective at short term kills they are ineffective on persistent antimicrobial activity and they complicate good skin hygiene by systematically destroying the acid mantle of the skin. Most people don't realize that although alcohol is known as a Class 1 Antiseptic it has a very short kill time maybe only 10-15 seconds. If you read the medical articles which support the use of alcohol based products you will find that in order to gain an "effective kill" you need to use at least 5ml's on your hands. Most applications by individuals barely reach 1ml. These products are temporary and do not provide a sustainable germ resistant environment. Tattoo Goo Deep Cleansing Soap is formulated to provide a broad spectrum kill while at the same time being gentle on the skin. Unlike "green" soap this formula has a slightly acidic pH and contains a key ingredient which helps to buffer the skin while providing additional killing power. The key ingredient is PCMX-L a combination of Chloroxylenol (PCMX) and Sodium Laurel Sarcosinate(Lauricidin). Lauricidin is a derived from palm seed extract.

Coolntape 0248 Crepe Bandage
Description: Cool'n tape is the only complete, non-drug treatment for sprains, strains, aches, pains and other soft tissue injuries. Where there are a variety of compression bandages (i.e.Tensor), ice packs, ice pack wraps (Cryo-cuff), oil and alcohol infused dressings and plasters, and moist wraps that provide evaporative cooling, Cool'n tape is the only compression wrap that provides elastic compression and cool therapy - all in one! These two fundamental principles stem back from Hippocrates and are found within standard medical practice (R.I.C.E). Cool'n tape has an elastic compression similar to gauze or tensors, that will also allow swelling to expand the dressing for severe injuries, and prevent over tightening. The benefit of compression versus just an ice pack is that compression will resist edema (swelling) from occurring and damaging the surrounding tissues.On the other hand, the application of cold (4ºC-10ºC) tends to lend itself to a cold shock response by the tissue- shunting off blood flow and causing tissue hypothermia. Cool'n tape uses a water based gel system that self-regulates a temperature found scientifically to be optimal for cooling, between 15-18ºC. Unlike several plasters and evaporative wraps on the market, Cool'n tape not only provides the sensation of cold and cool temperatures, but it acts as a heat sink to draw heat away from the body. Inflammation causes heat and too much heat can lead to destructive biological mechanisms. Cool'n tape gradually and consistently pulls the heat away cooling the skin on average 8ºC, and in turn reduces blood flow allowing healing to persist in a controlled manner.Altogether Cool'n tape is a far superior product to its close competitors, lacking many of the adverse effects caused by similar products (reddening, irritation and skin dryness). It is the only hydrogel cooling wrap with a heat wicking technology that allows you to use the dressing both on and off the field. Unlike ice, Cool'n tape can be used in between exercising or even worn at the office for periods of an 1-2hs. It is reusable, non-toxic, affordable and safe for all ages. It is easy to apply by oneself and can be used without refrigeration - right out of the package! Whether you are a professional athlete or a weekend warrior Cool'n tape will help to speed up recovery from pain and inflammation.
